import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    plt.legend(['Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median())])
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=gender_counts.index, y=gender_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    education_counts = data['education_level'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(education_counts, labels=education_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of education levels among the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(education_counts.index, title="Education Levels", loc="best")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
